annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein S2; Has a specific developmental role during oogenesis and a general role in protein synthesis as a component of the small ribosomal subunit
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L24; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL24 family
